##Worried about the impact of the domestic epidemic, I returned early to school in South Korea, only to panic and flee back to China

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

From the moment I landed in Beijing and turned on my domestic mobile phone, the staff contacted me on the phone to keep an eye on our health and our connection with the CDC staff.

Dictation | Nan

Finishing | Ying Chen

The school informed us that we would start school on March 16, with two weeks of online classes, and then make a decision based on the new crown pneumonia outbreak. By this calculation, I seem to really want to be in the hotel online class, it is fortunate that the speed of the Internet here is good.

Today (March 11) is the fifth day since I was sent to this central isolation point on March 7. I have to take my temperature three times a day.

As soon as we got to Korea, there was an outbreak

I was a Chinese student studying in South Korea. I returned to my hometown on December 25 last year. I was happy for a few days. I went to see my family and friends. But it didn't take long to see the news about the unexplained pneumonia in Wuhan, which wasn't so scary at first, and then the news that the city had been shut down, and my family and I realized it was getting worse.

Yinchuan is relatively far from the focus of the epidemic, and the local population mobility is relatively small, the epidemic is not very serious. But for safety reasons, I stayed at home with my family and didn't get out much during the Spring Festival.

When I returned, I bought a round-trip ticket and planned to fly back to Seoul on February 26. Then, as the epidemic got worse, in early February, the airline suddenly texted me that my scheduled flight had been canceled.

At that time, my school informed me that the opening of the school on March 2 would not change, and the confirmed cases in Korea were indeed very few. I came back with two fellow students decided to return to Korea as early as possible after consultation, because I do not know what the next domestic epidemic development, in case of the latter South Korean border restrictions on the trouble. None of us want to give up our studies. We face the double loss of money and time.

At that time many domestic and foreign flights were canceled, the airline hotline several times are busy, the change of booking process is very difficult, I began to call during the day on weekdays, hands-free and other manual customer service, more than 2 hours no answer. Later, I called at two or three in the morning, and even then I had to wait about 40 minutes.

Finally, we were able to buy a flight to Seoul via Shanghai on February 19. Due to the flight reduction, after arriving in Shanghai, the airline arranged for us to stay in a hotel for one night before flying to Seoul the next day. During the whole trip, my friends and I wore shower caps as well as face masks.

The moment we bought the ticket, we felt lucky. But when we got to Korea, we were completely blindsided. Confirmed cases began to cluster in South Korea on February 19, and the outbreak began on the day we arrived. South Korean officials initially reported little attention, only a few strokes. If we'd known, we'd have stayed back home.

Line at Seoul airport

The tension began the moment they entered the country. In addition to filling out an "infection declaration form, " each person would download an APP and declare their health status every day, in particular, the airport opened up a "chinese-only" channel, the impression is that this is the longest waiting time for an entry.

The one on the left is an overfilled infection declaration

There are about a dozen pharmacies near where we live. After unpacking, the three of US decided to stock up on masks and alcohol, which were no longer available and the last two bottles of alcohol in the area.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The last two bottles of alcohol and the family's hand sanitizer

As for the crucial mask, we bought it at a nearby drugstore the next day when we went to Myeong-dong to exchange money. The price of KF94 masks, which cost between 500 and 1,000 won each, has risen to nearly 3,000 won (18 yuan) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
KF94 masks that were still available

Slowly, we felt the growing severity of the outbreak in South Korea.

My school has been postponed until March 16th. Originally, the school stipulated that all international students must report to the school and hand in their forms when they arrive in South Korea, but since the school is in another city 70 or 80 kilometers away from Seoul, it seems to me that I should go out as little as possible from China; on the other hand, i was also very alarmed by the lack of disinfection of public transport and the large number of people who did not wear face masks in South Korea, and the school teacher eventually agreed that we should pay them back after school started, given the risk of infection on the roads.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 25, a coupon for an EMART's face mask was given out, but there were still consumers gathering at the site | Korean website

With more than 20 days to go, we bought some food supplies online and delivered them that night. But two days later, when we tried to buy food online again, we found that what was available one second was sold out the next, and even the delivery could only be booked two days later.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 20, the day we arrived in South Korea, there were also young people on the subway who did not wear masks

The percentage of people on the road who don't wear masks has gone from more than 50 percent the day we landed to about 10 percent.

Meanwhile, my friend forgot to declare on the APP one day and immediately received a text message warning: "If you fail to declare on time, you will face a penalty of 1 million won. ". In addition, every day cell phone will receive seven or eight about the outbreak of news.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
An automated outbreak alert text

I was the last one to board the plane

There are two things that really made us decide to go back to China -- Florida -- one was a confirmed case in South Korea who visited our grocery store, the other was the news on March 2nd that about 100 flights to and from China would be cut each week, then there is the large-scale grounding, South Korea back to Qingdao economy class ticket prices rose to more than 3,000 yuan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers Walk past a hospital in Seoul, South Korea

At that time, we searched for a ticket back to Yinchuan, only 1,000 yuan, not much increase in price. The three of us were booked on a March 7 flight back to Yinchuan, either on a different flight or at a loss of a few hundred dollars. The airline then informed us that our original flight had been cancelled, but as a result we were rescheduled to the same time the day before.

Because it is not a connecting flight, the transit time between the two flights is less than two hours, we do not check baggage. But that day was spent in line and on the run.

Beijing airport

Although the number of tourists is not the most, when we enter the diplomatic courtesy channel to our personnel to go abroad, but the entry of inspection and Quarantine is very strict, three times on the temperature measurement. I glimpsed a man in a mask at the mobile quarantine point in the corner. Transfer, the border control staff asked very carefully, security check, the staff took out all the liquid bag, one by one to ask what is, but also open smell to confirm again.

We didn't get to the gate until 15 minutes before the plane took off. The ground crew took my temperature a couple of times, but it was too high. She told me to cool off or she wouldn't let me on the plane. And two of my friends are already on board. I was sweating profusely, throwing my bag on the floor and taking off my jacket, then fanning myself. With three minutes to go, my temperature finally returned to normal, and I was the last person on the flight.

Straight from the airport to mass quarantine

In fact, the day we bought our tickets, we told our family that we were coming back, and the family reported it to the community and the police. The community and the police station pay great attention to those who come back from abroad. They call my family every day to find out about me. From the moment I landed in Beijing and turned on my domestic mobile phone, the staff contacted me on the phone to keep an eye on our health and our connection with the CDC staff.

Quarantine area of Yinchuan Airport

Before we even hit the ground, the Yinchuan CDC was waiting for us at the airport exit in Hazmat suits. They had US wait in a quarantine zone at the airport, and the three of us were taken to a designated quarantine point along with two other Korean returnees and one German returnee.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hotel Room

The hotel is in good condition. Everyone has a standard room. The Three Meals a Day, the supplies are all there. If we need anything, we'll let the staff know. It's just that there's a lot of control here, and my family used to send me stuff, and it had to go outside the lockdown zone, and somebody from there gave it to the hotel people, and then they told me to go to the lobby.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For The New York City Police Department

Friends live next door, although we can not visit, but at least we can talk through the wall, because the sound insulation here is a bit poor.

Now, I just want to take online classes for two weeks before saying, anyway, "worst case" result is suspension this semester, then the school should also have policy, so it is not very panic, to be able to return to the country is already very satisfied.
